02/03/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A conference on human trafficking and illegal migration opened in Skopje on Thursday (March 1st), and was attended by government and police officials, NGOs and representatives of international community.
In his opening speech, Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski stressed that the fight against organised crime and implementing the rule of law are the main goals of his cabinet.
He insisted on better co-ordination, not only with international police and security services but among all domestic institutions.
(MIA, Makfax - 01/03/07)
